<p><strong>COOKIES PRIVACY POLICY</strong><br><br>
This website uses “cookies” to improve your browsing experience. Cookies are information (short code strings) that are temporarily archived in your browser’s memory. The data collected through cookies allow to compare old and new visitors, understand how users browse through the website, and generally improve the website experience. For any information concerning the use of cookies, please write to: <a href="mailto:info@wexplore.eu">info@wexplore.eu</a>.</p>
<p>The cookies of this website <strong>do not record any personal information on the user</strong>, and any identifiable data will not be memorized. Should you wish to disable the use of cookies, we advise you to customize the settings of your computer by selecting the option to cancel all cookies or to activate a notification message when cookies are memorized. To proceed without changing the cookie application, simply continue browsing the website. Visit AboutCookies.org for any further information on cookies and on how they influence your navigation experience. </p>
<p><u>A. COOKIES IN USE</u><br>
  <strong>1. Mandatory Cookies</strong><br>
  These cookies are essential for browsing the entire website and using all of its functionalities, including the various protected areas within the website. Without these cookies, some of the services, including the access to and functioning of online services, cannot be enjoyed. <br>
  <strong>2. Performance Cookies</strong><br>
  The present website utilizes also the so-called “performance cookies” to support us in gaining information on how many people read the website, how many pages are opened, where the users come from, which are the most visited pages, and whether users incur in any error message. These cookies do not gather information that allow to identify a specific user. All information collected through cookies are aggregate and therefore anonymous. Their sole purpose is to improve the functioning of a website (through Google Analytics services, adequately anonymized). By going through our website, the user accepts that such cookies may be memorized on his/her device. <br>
  <strong>3. Functionality Cookies</strong><br>
  Cookies allow the website to memorize the choices made by the user (such as the preferred language) and provide advanced customized functionalities. These cookies can be used also to memorize changes in text size, fonts, and other customizable web pages. The information collected by these cookies can be made anonymous and disabled from monitoring your browsing activity on other websites. By navigating on our website, the user accepts that such cookies may be installed on his/her device. These cookies are not currently employed, but we reserve the right to do so in the future.</p>
<p><u>B. THIRD PARTY COOKIES</u><br>
The cookies adopted by third parties are employed to retrieve completely anonymous and aggregate statistics for the owner or the third party providers. The third party providers of such cookies, and of the related information, are:
- <strong>Disqus</strong>: The website uses Disqus for managing the comments to the published posts. The use of such service involves the installation of cookies, including profiling cookies, from the third party offering such services, as indicated in the privacy policy available at the following link:
<a href="https://help.disqus.com/customer/portal/articles/466259-privacy-policy">link</a>.<br>
The data collected by this kind of cookies are visible to the owner only in aggregate form, and adequately anonymized. The user can opt out in any moment for what concerns the collection of information performed by this cookies, as indicated at the following <a href="https://help.disqus.com/customer/portal/articles/1657951-ad-training-settings?utm_source=disqus&utm_medium=forumset-tracking&utm_content=txt">link</a><br>
  - <strong>Google Analytics</strong>: anonymous statistical cookies - <a href="http://www.google.it/policies/privacy/partners">see the privacy policy here</a> in order to disable the analytical cookies and prevent Google Analytics from monitoring them through every website, it is possible to download Google Analytics Out as an addition component of the browser: tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout.
These cookies are not owned by the Website Owner. Should you prefer that Google Analytics will not make any use of the collected data, we suggest you to: a) use the “Do Not Track” option of your browser to navigate incognito; in order to activate said option, consult the browser you are currently using: Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Apple Safari; or b) choose to disable Google Analytics on your browser by installing the specific disabling component.<br>
  <strong><u>- Social network buttons and widgets.</u></strong><br>
  Social Buttons are the social network icons displayed on the website (including Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter), and allow the website users to interact through a simple mouse click on the associated social platforms.  <br>
The Social Buttons used on the website in the contact sections are links to the Owner’s accounts on the displayed social networks. The use of such buttons implies that no third party cookies are installed on the website. The site incorporates widgets from Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn. The use of such services involves the installation of profiling cookies by the above mentioned companies. As in the case of anonymized Google Analytics, no information is shared on the website hosting the social network’s widget.  <br>
For further information, including how to disable such cookies, please refer to the following links:
<br>
- <a href="https://www.facebook.com/policies/cookies/">https://www.facebook.com/policies/cookies/</a><br>
- <a href="https://support.twitter.com/articles/20170519">https://support.twitter.com/articles/20170519</a><br>
- <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/cookie-policy">https://www.linkedin.com/legal/cookie-policy</a><br>
- <a href="https://help.disqus.com/customer/portal/articles/466259-privacy-policy">https://help.disqus.com/customer/portal/articles/466259-privacy-policy</a>.<br>
Notwithstanding what has been specified above, the owner informs the user that he/she can opt for Your Online Choices. Through this service it is possible to manage the tracing preferences of most advertising tools. The owner, therefore, recommends the users to use such tool, in addition to the information provided herewith.</p>
<p><u>C. DISABLING COOKIES</u><br>
Most browsers automatically accept cookies and allow the possibility to control them through their settings, even when the user is not obliged to accept them. All cookies can be disabled also by modifying the browser’s settings, according to the related procedure. Please find below useful suggestions to perform this operation:  http://www.wikihow.com/Disable-Cookies. Please note that disabling some cookies may alter the correct functioning of the website.
The user may verify which cookies are installed and for how long, and eliminate them. The steps to perform such operations differ for each browser. We therefore suggest to verify the instructions for your browser. Please find below the links to the instructions for the most common browsers in use: <br>
  Chrome - <a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/32050?hl=it">https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/32050?hl=it</a><br>
  Firefox - <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/">https://support.mozilla.org/</a><br>
  Safari - <a href="https://www.apple.com/support/mac-apps/safari/">https://www.apple.com/support/mac-apps/safari/</a><br>
  Internet Explorer - <a href="http://support.microsoft.com/product/internet-explorer/internet-explorer-11">http://support.microsoft.com/product/internet-explorer/internet-explorer-11</a> <br>
  Opera - <a href="http://www.opera.com/help">http://www.opera.com/help</a>.</p>
